text.section:
In this section, "motor home" means a motor vehicle that:
Is designed to provide temporary living quarters, built into as an integral part of, or permanently attached to, a self-propelled motor vehicle chassis or van; and
Contains permanently installed independent life support systems which provide at least four of the following facilities:
Cooking;
Refrigeration or ice box;
Self-contained toilet;
Heating, air-conditioning, or both;
A potable water supply system including a faucet and sink;
Separate 110-125 volt electrical power supply; or
An LP gas supply.
